1
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:36,320
- <i>What do you want?</i>
<i>- Don't think you can mess with me</i>

2
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,360
and get away with it. You're going to pay.

3
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:41,480
- What? Wait.
- It's real.

4
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:44,400
Sorry. I'm sorry, babe.

5
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:48,120
Damn it! They've taken all the money!

6
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,640
I told you these brats would come back.

7
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:51,360
- Risa.
- Hey!

8
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:53,600
<i>Welcome, everyone.</i>

9
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,880
<i>From now on, call me</i>

10
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:58,120
- <i>Admin.</i>
- Follow Admin's plan.

11
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:00,200
You get rid of your enemy

12
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:02,040
and get paid a fortune too.

13
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:03,560
<i>Admin's plan</i>

14
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:05,800
<i>is to use all your skills</i>

15
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:08,479
<i>to set up a boxing bet for Boss Kluay,</i>
<i>the thing he knows best.</i>

16
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:11,200
Make him believe
he's about to win a massive payout.

17
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:13,240
And the moment he brings that money out…

18
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:14,800
That money disappears

19
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:15,800
and ends up with us instead.

20
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:19,320
Hey, is everything ready?

21
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,800
All set. Should I post it now?

22
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:22,800
Go for it.

23
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:24,800
‪EDIT MORE, NEXT

24
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,320
Boss.

25
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,240
The IG account you told me
to monitor just posted.

26
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:34,880
This is the ten million for Louis.
Put it in the safe.

27
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:35,960
That bastard's gonna call
and ask for it again.

28
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:38,120
Yes, sir. Here you go.

29
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:40,920
MR. JACKY WONG POSTS

30
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:55,000
<i>Maybe Wong could be the one</i>
<i>who helps us break free</i>

31
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:56,600
<i>from Louis sooner.</i>

32
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:05,040
Absolutely, boss. I guarantee this deal

33
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,880
will make you so rich, you'll forget

34
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:08,600
all the bad blood between us.

35
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:10,880
Why are you talking so much?

36
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:13,120
Hey. Boss Kluay took the bait.

37
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,720
Get ready for the next step.

38
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,440
- Yes!
- Yeah!

39
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,760
- Come on!
- Yay!

40
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:25,040
Hey, Chen. Didn't you hear?

41
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,360
The next step.

42
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,080
- The next step?
- Yeah.

43
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,520
What is it?

44
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,040
It's your turn now.

45
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,360
Go change and take some photos.

46
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:52,560
Hello.

47
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:54,200
You can speak Thai?

48
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,520
I can speak a little Thai.

49
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,560
But I can't speak English at all.

50
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:04,600
Not funny.

51
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,640
I used to have a Thai wife,

52
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:12,520
so I can speak a little Thai.

53
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:15,760
But I'm about to have another wife,

54
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:18,920
so I'll probably get even better at it.

55
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,120
Boss, you're always joking.

56
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,680
I think we should head inside.

57
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:26,760
Yes.

58
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,160
Hey, you brought the whole gang with you?

59
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,520
We're here to carve up the pig, boss.

60
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:49,600
Strange.

61
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:52,720
It's just a regular boxing gym.
Why do they need this many guards?

62
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:56,200
Okay, we're right outside the boxing gym.

63
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:03,760
- Got it yet, Angpao?
- One sec.

64
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,160
Done. I'm connected to the CCTV system.

65
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,520
Is this what you did to Cocoa Cafe?

66
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,800
Yes.

67
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:16,320
Koh, the main computer
should be in this room.

68
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,440
Here, Koh.

69
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,880
Hey, you charged the battery, right?

70
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:30,440
Trust me. No problems, guaranteed.

71
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:37,760
Keep watch.

72
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,440
If anything seems off,
radio me right away.

73
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:43,080
Yeah.

74
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:46,560
No matter what it is,
radio me right away. Got it?

75
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:49,480
I know. It's such an easy job.

76
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:52,600
If you're scared, I can go in instead.

77
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:13,080
Your boxing arena

78
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,080
is pretty nice.

79
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,200
Thank you.

80
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,560
But mine back home is even nicer.

81
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:23,720
Too bad there's no match today.

82
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,600
I thought I'd get to place a bet with you.

83
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,960
I heard you own a boxing camp in China.

84
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:32,000
I know a little about that world too.

85
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,360
May I ask which camp you're from?

86
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,040
The camp name?

87
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:46,520
The name is…

88
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:49,840
Damn it. Don't tell me you forgot, Pae.

89
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:50,920
I think he forgot.

90
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,080
Well, Mr. Wong?

91
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,280
Where's my bag?

92
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,400
It's right here.

93
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,040
Here you go.

94
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,080
Huang Ho Boxing.

95
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,720
That's a huge camp.

96
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,360
So why don't I recognize
your name, Mr. Wong?

97
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:20,640
I don't really make public appearances.

98
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:23,640
And besides, I'm not primarily a promoter.

99
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:26,480
Unless it's a really big fight.

100
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,720
Oh, is that so?

101
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:30,840
Where's the bathroom?

102
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,080
I'll have my guy take you.

103
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:34,800
- Take him to the bathroom.
- Yes, sir.

104
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,080
- This way, please.
- Alright.

105
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:40,560
So what now?

106
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:43,280
Boss, what's so hard about this?
Just have your guys beat him up

107
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:45,040
and take his money.

108
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,360
Are you stupid?

109
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:49,360
There's probably only a million
in that bag.

110
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:52,080
That's not enough to cover
what you took from my mom.

111
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:03,800
Didn't you say he was loaded?

112
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:04,800
He is, boss.

113
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,640
That guy's worth hundreds of millions.

114
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,720
Here's my plan.

115
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,320
Look at this.

116
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,200
This bastard's one of your guys.

117
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:22,480
His name's Chen.

118
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:25,240
He used to be a boxer.
He fought in China and got really famous.

119
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,840
Wong likes him.

120
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,160
So what?

121
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:30,440
Challenge him to a bet.

122
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:32,039
Then I'll have Chen

123
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:34,200
throw the fight. He'll do it.

124
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,679
He owes you money, doesn't he?

125
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:39,200
- What are you guys talking about?
- Oh, they were talking about Chen.

126
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:42,840
Which Chen?

127
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,680
That's Unchain!

128
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:52,840
I haven't seen him fight in ages.

129
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:54,040
Does he still fight?

130
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,600
Of course he does.

131
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:58,120
You could have the boss arrange
a fight with Chen.

132
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,560
When it comes to the boxing world,

133
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,120
he knows everyone.

134
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:06,800
If you can get Unchain to fight,
Mr. Kluay,

135
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,240
that would be amazing.

136
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:12,200
If I can get Unchain to fight,

137
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:16,520
would you be interested
in putting some money on it, Mr. Wong?

138
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:26,840
This is a lucky ring from Che Kung Temple.

139
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:29,960
This model goes for millions.

140
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:35,160
If you can wear it,

141
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,960
I'll accept your offer, Mr. Kluay.

142
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,200
Yeah, I'll head down now. Okay.

143
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:36,480
I found the room.

144
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:38,440
Turn on the computer
and plug in the flash drive.

145
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:39,520
I'll handle the rest.

146
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:50,800
I got rich because of Unchain.

147
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:54,120
If it's Unchain, I'll bet any amount.

148
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,760
But I'm betting on Unchain's side.

149
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:00,080
- You okay with that?
- Either way's fine with me.

150
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:02,200
Whatever you're comfortable with.

151
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:04,320
My fighter's skills

152
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,680
are no joke either.

153
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,840
Well then.

154
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:13,800
Let me know.

155
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:27,080
Is this ring really worth millions?

156
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:28,520
Look it up.

157
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,920
Che Kung Temple,

158
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,600
located in the province--

159
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:40,080
- I didn't tell you to look up the temple.
- Boss!

160
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:42,080
Look up that boxer Unchain!

161
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:44,880
I'm sorry, boss.
I'll search again right away.

162
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,800
Hey, he told someone
to check Chen's background.

163
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,040
He's checking Chen's background.

164
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,800
<i>Is everything ready over there?</i>

165
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,880
Almost, sis. Shouldn't be a problem.

166
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:10,880
By the way, did the bug work?

167
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:14,440
Of course. I was waiting to see
what trick Pae would pull.

168
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:16,000
Pretty smooth, right?

169
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:18,440
Che Kung Temple is real,

170
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:21,160
but they don't make rings
with GPS trackers

171
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,440
and bugs inside them.

172
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:27,520
I can't find any record
of a boxer named Unchain online, boss.

173
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,840
Maybe they're underground fighters.

174
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:33,200
Never mind.

175
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:35,200
- We'll head back and check at the gym.
- Yes.

176
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:40,120
Kluay's heading back to the gym.
Are you done yet?

177
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,240
- The flash drive's plugged in.
- Copy that.

178
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,920
I'm remoting in to crack the password.

179
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,200
Can you hear me?
The flash drive's plugged in.

180
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:55,520
Copy that. I'm remoting in
to crack the password.

181
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:01,920
What?

182
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:05,600
The fighters' records
aren't on this computer.

183
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,400
You checked thoroughly, right?

184
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,880
I'm sure. There's nothing here.

185
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:14,160
That means the data's on another computer.

186
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:16,920
Pao, pull up the building layout.

187
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:22,200
Here. The third floor.
It should be Boss Kluay's office.

188
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,880
Third floor, Koh.

189
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:27,040
<i>Third floor, Boss Kluay's office.</i>

190
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:29,760
Repeat. Third floor, the office--

191
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,800
Hello? Third floor, which room?

192
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:35,360
- Hello?
- Hello?

193
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:39,880
Did you fully charge this thing?

194
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,320
Koh!

195
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:55,600
How's it going? Boss Kluay's almost here.

196
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:00,680
What? What happened?

197
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:27,960
Hello, Koh?

198
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,280
Hello? Koh?

199
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,280
I can't reach him at all.

200
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,880
He probably can't hear us anymore.

201
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:38,120
Everybody, calm down. I'll call Koh.

202
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:47,920
Oh. He left his phone.

203
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:50,320
- What do we do now?
- What do we do?

204
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,120
He'll be back in less than ten minutes.

205
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:58,880
- Then I'll go in myself.
- No!

206
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:02,120
If you get caught,
the whole plan falls apart too.

207
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,880
Did you forget? You have to be Unchain.

208
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,440
I'll go myself.

209
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:08,840
- Hey, Ris!
- Hold on! Don't!

210
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:10,680
- Ris!
- Wait! No!

211
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:12,400
If you go, who's going to help Angpao?

212
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,840
But Ris…

213
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,880
Which room is it?

214
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:26,960
All set, bro.

215
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:29,480
Got it.

216
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:32,200
I'll turn on the AC
for the boss right away.

217
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,560
‪KIAT SAMKOR BOXING CAMP

218
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:22,560
Hurry up. Go find
Unchain's background for me.

219
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:23,960
Yes, boss.

220
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,480
I hope that fatso sees this.

221
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:40,480
- It connected!
- What?

222
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:43,600
It connected! Koh plugged the drive
into the computer!

223
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:46,600
Pao, don't celebrate yet. Hurry up.

224
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:48,120
Transfer the data first.

225
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:54,400
‪KIAT SAMKOR BOXING CAMP

226
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:01,800
- Wait.
- Yes?

227
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:03,320
The car bringing the kids…

228
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:04,839
Is it gonna screw us over again?

229
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,319
It should get here tonight.

230
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,319
They probably won't dare
back out on us again.

231
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,240
Good.

232
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:41,680
Boss Kluay's coming up. Hide, quick.

233
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:54,960
I'll go get you some water.

234
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:57,240
- No need. Go turn on the computer.
- Yes, sir.

235
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:59,600
Check if Unchain's name
is in the fighter records.

236
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:00,640
Yes.

237
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:10,840
Boss.

238
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:12,640
The computer's already on.

239
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:31,560
I probably told Nop to turn on
both the computer and the AC.

240
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:34,720
Then hurry up and check.

241
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:50,640
Let go.

242
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:55,720
Found it, boss.

243
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:58,680
He really is with Huang Ho Boxing.

244
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:00,760
Print it out.

245
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:08,960
Here you go, boss.

246
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:12,400
His record's nothing special.

247
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,440
Why's Mr. Wong so confident

248
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:16,080
this guy's got something?

249
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:19,480
What?

250
00:19:20,080 --> 00:19:21,680
Okay, I'll come down.

251
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:23,400
The car with the kids is here.

252
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,480
- Geez.
- Ugh.

253
00:19:36,520 --> 00:19:39,680
- Don't do that again. I don't like it.
- Then why'd you get goosebumps?

254
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,160
Hurry up. Get out.

255
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:52,120
Where have you been?

256
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:58,560
Well, boss.

257
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,160
We got quite a haul this time.

258
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,320
I asked you where you've been.

259
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,840
Don't tell me

260
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:20,560
you already broke them all in.

261
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:21,960
Come on, boss.

262
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:24,320
Their parents sent them here
to pay off their debts.

263
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:26,160
They were gonna be sold anyway.

264
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:28,840
Sooner or later, it was bound to happen.

265
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,520
"Sooner or later, it was bound to happen"?

266
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:32,400
Here!

267
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:37,320
- You want them seeing us? Move!
- You damaged the goods.

268
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,640
You understand?

269
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:41,840
What the hell's wrong with you?

270
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:44,680
Take them all away!

271
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:50,000
Come on! Move!

272
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:51,240
Move!

273
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:54,720
Come on! Hurry!

274
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:56,440
- Hurry!
- No!

275
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:57,960
- Move!
- I'm not going!

276
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:05,200
<i>Those children were taken by Boss Kluay</i>

277
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:07,120
<i>and forced to work off</i>
<i>their parents' debts.</i>

278
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:09,440
<i>The strong ones are trained as fighters.</i>

279
00:21:09,520 --> 00:21:11,160
<i>The rest are used as beggars,</i>

280
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:12,680
<i>illegal laborers,</i>

281
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:14,440
<i>and even forced into sex work.</i>

282
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,320
So what?

283
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,600
Are we just supposed to let this happen
and do nothing?

284
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:20,920
<i>And that's another reason</i>

285
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:22,640
<i>I want to take them down.</i>

286
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:26,200
<i>I'm not trying to be a hero.</i>

287
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:28,240
<i>I'm not playing vigilante.</i>

288
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:30,360
<i>But when evil people's greed</i>

289
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:32,640
<i>makes society this rotten,</i>

290
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:37,120
<i>scamming them back a little</i>
<i>shouldn't be so wrong.</i>

291
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:41,200
This guy sounds pretty righteous.

292
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:43,880
I think he's actually doing it
for justice.

293
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:48,920
You heard that, right?

294
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:53,200
We need to take out Kluay first.
That's the only way to save those kids.

295
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:55,840
If we move too fast and go off-plan,

296
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:57,280
we'll all end up dead.

297
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:58,480
Hey.

298
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:01,800
Just saying. You can take it if you want.

299
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:05,120
Hey, stop!

300
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:06,600
It's your first job,
and you're already fighting?

301
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:10,440
Kluay's calling!

302
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:12,040
What is it, Hong?

303
00:22:12,120 --> 00:22:14,400
BOSS KLUAY

304
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,520
Hello? What's up, boss?

305
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,680
Get Unchain ready.

306
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:22,320
I'm putting him in the ring
against White Shark

307
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:26,320
at K-Fight next week.

308
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:27,560
Absolutely.

309
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:29,600
I'll let Mr. Wong know right away.

310
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:31,520
Oh, boss. About Chen,

311
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:34,520
do you want him to throw the fight
from the first round?

312
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:39,000
You really think that Chinese-looking
dessert shop guy

313
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:40,800
can beat my champion, White Shark?

314
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,800
Tell him

315
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:44,600
to fight with everything he's got.

316
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:46,480
I want to see that smug look

317
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:49,800
wiped off Wong's face.

318
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:56,120
- Whatever makes you happy.
- Yeah.

319
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:58,200
- Soon we'll see who's embarrassed.
- Come on!

320
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:00,400
Okay. Everything's falling into place.

321
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,440
Alright. Good luck, everyone.

322
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:08,320
- Let's go brief Pae and get him ready.
- Okay.

323
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,160
Let's go.

324
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:12,680
Hey, wait.

325
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:15,120
What did I just hear? Chen? Unchain? What?

326
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:17,160
Do I have to box? Do I have to fight?

327
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:19,600
- Do I have to throw the fight?
- Weren't you listening?

328
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:21,200
He said fight with everything you've got.

329
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,760
So just fight hard. Go all out.

330
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:25,760
How am I not supposed to think about it?

331
00:23:26,280 --> 00:23:27,880
I still don't get it.

332
00:23:29,320 --> 00:23:30,360
Ris.

333
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:31,920
- Let's go, Angpao.
- What's with her?

334
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,120
- Hey, hold on.
- Yes?

335
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:35,920
Everything they said

336
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,760
doesn't sound that hard.
But somehow, it feels really bad.

337
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:42,000
Here, watch this.

338
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:42,920
‪Here.

339
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,760
White Shark, Chen.

340
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:51,280
He hits that hard?

341
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:52,760
I don't think I can do this.

342
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:56,240
Guard up.

343
00:23:56,320 --> 00:23:58,200
Guard up. Come on!

344
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:59,800
- One, two!
- Three, four!

345
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:04,480
Punch. You're supposed to punch. One, two!

346
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:14,600
Get ready. Training starts tomorrow.
I'll be your coach.

347
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,560
Trust me.

348
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:30,960
Higher! Just a little higher!

349
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:33,000
Higher!

350
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:37,360
‪Almost there!

351
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:42,480
Hey, where are you going?

352
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:54,240
Harder! What a waste of those muscles.

353
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:56,240
Come on. Punch hard! Finish it!

354
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:04,480
Keep going!

355
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:35,120
Turn around.

356
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,320
Try this shirt.

357
00:25:48,040 --> 00:25:49,360
Come out here.

358
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:50,560
What do you think, boss?

359
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,600
- 995!
- Come on!

360
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:37,920
- 996!
- Don't give up!

361
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,360
- 997!
- You're almost there.

362
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,280
998!

363
00:26:40,360 --> 00:26:43,320
Go, go, go!

364
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:42,600
Hey, buddy. How is it?

365
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:44,560
Seeing it gets you fired up, right?

366
00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:54,240
Wait, Hong.

367
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:56,040
You spent forever picking Pae's outfit.

368
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:59,080
Why is he wearing the same thing,
with just a scarf added?

369
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:01,560
I tried everything.
This one looked the best.

370
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:03,320
Isn't it too loose?

371
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:49,640
So, how much are we betting?

372
00:28:50,320 --> 00:28:52,560
Anything's fine with me.
I'm bringing in a champion.

373
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:54,080
How much of an edge
do you want me to give you, Mr. Wong?

374
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:59,120
I have faith in Unchain.

375
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:01,200
Let's make it even.

376
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:02,320
You really want it even?

377
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:06,280
So how much should we bet?

378
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:08,560
Five million?

379
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:09,920
No problem.

380
00:29:26,320 --> 00:29:27,240
Hey.

381
00:29:47,520 --> 00:29:49,120
And from this moment on,

382
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:50,640
<i>this will be a special title match</i>

383
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:54,040
<i>in the K-Fight Arena Kings event.</i>

384
00:29:54,120 --> 00:29:55,920
Our challenger has a long fight record.

385
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:58,200
Out of 119 fights,

386
00:29:58,280 --> 00:30:00,080
<i>he has 85 wins,</i>

387
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:03,320
<i>25 losses, and nine draws.</i>

388
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:06,280
Known as "The Vengeful Fighter",

389
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:09,080
Unchain from Huang Ho Boxing Gym!

390
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:13,360
- Unchain!
- Unchain!

391
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:15,200
Let's go!

392
00:30:18,360 --> 00:30:22,240
Unchain!

393
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:24,320
- Win this.
- You'll die, you know.

394
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:25,960
Unchain!

395
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:28,200
Can you handle it? You could die!

396
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:31,120
Unchain!

397
00:30:32,480 --> 00:30:34,880
Go on. Go! Hurry up!

398
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:36,640
Chen, go!

399
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:38,640
- Go!
- Unchain!

400
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:40,040
You okay?

401
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:42,120
Don't hold back. Go!

402
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:43,480
Go! Hurry up!

403
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:52,280
- You can do it.
- Our two-time champion and crowd favorite!

404
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:54,440
Let's hear it

405
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:57,000
for "The Killer Fin", White Shark

406
00:30:57,080 --> 00:30:59,320
from Kiat Samkor!

407
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:13,160
Come on. Fight hard!

408
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:17,200
Be confident, Chen.

409
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:21,360
- Guard up.
- Round one.

410
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:25,200
Ready. Fight!

411
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:30,960
Come on! Keep your guard up!

412
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:34,200
Keep your guard up! Be confident, Chen!

413
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:40,840
Go, Chen!

414
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:54,840
Looks like you're losing
your bet already, Mr. Wong.

415
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:02,000
Why is he still so confident?

416
00:32:02,080 --> 00:32:03,440
Does he even know boxing?

417
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:05,880
- Come on, Chen!
- Hey, Chen!

418
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:08,280
Chen! Get up!

419
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:09,720
- Get up!
- Come on!

420
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:11,520
- Get up!
- Chen!

421
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:14,240
- Get up now!
- Chen! Hurry!

422
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:17,400
Get up, Chen!

423
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:19,360
Get up, quick, Chen!

424
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:21,040
- Will he get up in time?
- Yeah!

425
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:22,240
You're still in this!

426
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:23,560
You okay?

427
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:24,800
- Gao.
- Huh?

428
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:27,520
Is this plan you cooked up with Pae
really going to work?

429
00:32:28,120 --> 00:32:30,000
You don't cook the pig
before the water boils.

430
00:32:32,440 --> 00:32:34,240
You okay? Fight!

431
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:38,840
Guard up! Go!

432
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:42,240
- Hey! Chen!
- Don't get cornered!

433
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:45,640
- Dodge!
- Don't get cornered!

434
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:47,480
Don't drop your guard!

435
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:48,840
- Don't get cornered!
- Hey!

436
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:51,920
Move! Get out!

437
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:55,960
Get up! Get up first!

438
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:03,840
- Sit down.
- How are you feeling, Chen?

439
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:04,880
Can you keep going?

440
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:08,480
Looks like he's done, Mr. Wong.

441
00:33:08,560 --> 00:33:11,040
Unchain isn't looking too good.

442
00:33:12,320 --> 00:33:14,640
We Chinese believe falling

443
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:15,720
doesn't mean you've lost.

444
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:22,000
Gao, didn't you say you had a way
to lure money out of him?

445
00:33:22,080 --> 00:33:23,160
Wait for the right moment.

446
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:24,400
What moment?

447
00:33:27,760 --> 00:33:31,640
The moment he lets his guard down.

448
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:43,960
I think we'll have to wait

449
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:46,040
several more rounds
before we know who wins.

450
00:33:46,840 --> 00:33:48,120
Why don't we make things

451
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:50,040
more interesting?

452
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:53,720
What do you mean?

453
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:55,920
If you're trying to switch sides
and bet on White Shark,

454
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:58,240
- I won't allow it.
- No.

455
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:02,240
I'm still 100% confident in Unchain.

456
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:06,480
I'd like to raise the bet.

457
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:10,840
By the next round,

458
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:13,920
Unchain will TKO White Shark.

459
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:17,760
You want to add another bet

460
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:20,320
that Unchain will knock out White Shark

461
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:21,440
in round two?

462
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:25,199
Correct.

463
00:34:26,239 --> 00:34:28,199
One more million.

464
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:37,120
Hey, wait. Pae's betting another million?

465
00:34:37,199 --> 00:34:39,639
Chen can barely manage
to land one clean punch on him

466
00:34:39,719 --> 00:34:41,000
as it is.

467
00:34:41,080 --> 00:34:43,960
The water's boiling, idiot. Let go.

468
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:45,440
Hey, man.

469
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:53,440
What do you say, Mr. Kluay?

470
00:34:56,520 --> 00:34:57,920
No problem.

471
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,600
Hey, bring the money.

472
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:12,320
Go tell Chen.

473
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:15,360
He has to last as long as he can.
He absolutely cannot lose. Hurry.

474
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:25,480
Okay, got it, Uncle. I'll tell him.

475
00:35:25,560 --> 00:35:26,440
Yeah.

476
00:35:26,520 --> 00:35:27,800
Hey!

477
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:30,560
The guys upstairs said
to stall for time. Don't lose yet.

478
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:34,280
- What? Stall for time and don't lose?
- Yeah.

479
00:35:34,360 --> 00:35:36,600
You said I should wait
for the signal to throw the fight!

480
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:38,560
I don't know.
That's just what they told me.

481
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:39,600
Hey!

482
00:35:42,320 --> 00:35:43,600
I'm not surviving this.

483
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:45,480
Just look at White Shark's face.

484
00:35:46,200 --> 00:35:48,560
Okay, listen, Chen.
Don't get close to him.

485
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:51,360
Jab and back off. Focus on dodging.

486
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:52,760
But if it gets really bad…

487
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:54,000
- This is bad!
- Run!

488
00:35:55,640 --> 00:35:59,080
Yeah, run! Run from him.
Just keep circling him.

489
00:35:59,160 --> 00:36:00,600
It might look pathetic,

490
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:02,440
but you'll survive. Got it?

491
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:07,240
Fight!

492
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:08,440
Let's go!

493
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:11,960
- Guard up!
- Don't drop your guard!

494
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,160
Yeah!

495
00:36:13,240 --> 00:36:14,200
Go for it!

496
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,640
Guard up!

497
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:19,120
Chen!

498
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:21,280
Hit and back off! Don't you get it?

499
00:36:21,360 --> 00:36:23,120
Yeah, I got it!

500
00:36:25,560 --> 00:36:27,240
Hey! Use your legs!

501
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:29,000
- Hit and move! Don't stay in close!
- Guard up!

502
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:37,480
Keep circling. Yeah.

503
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:41,520
What the hell?

504
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:43,480
He's just running. We're gonna lose money.

505
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:47,640
Keep circling. Yeah, just like that!

506
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:51,600
- Guard up!
- Yeah!

507
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,040
Back to your corner!

508
00:36:57,760 --> 00:36:59,520
Good. That's good.

509
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:03,880
Mr. Kluay, you're really lucky.

510
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,280
Unchain didn't perform

511
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:07,200
very well this round.

512
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:08,520
I think

513
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:10,120
he didn't do anything at all.

514
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:11,720
That would be more accurate, Mr. Wong.

515
00:37:11,800 --> 00:37:13,920
But next round, he'll definitely do it!

516
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:19,320
What do you mean?

517
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:21,720
I'm betting another two million.

518
00:37:24,120 --> 00:37:26,800
There's five million in this bag.

519
00:37:26,880 --> 00:37:29,520
I only lost one million that round.

520
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:31,240
I still have plenty left.

521
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:33,280
I traveled all this way.

522
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:35,400
At least give me a chance to win it back.

523
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:37,680
Alright, I get it.

524
00:37:37,760 --> 00:37:39,360
But the reason I was shocked

525
00:37:39,440 --> 00:37:40,640
is because I can't believe

526
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:42,800
you still dare to bet on Unchain.

527
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:45,240
This round,

528
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:47,600
he's definitely knocking out White Shark!

529
00:37:51,080 --> 00:37:52,200
Let's keep going.

530
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:55,160
Go for it. Get in there.

531
00:37:55,240 --> 00:37:56,800
Do the same thing, Chen.

532
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:58,920
Don't get close.

533
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:01,680
That's right, Chen!

534
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:04,520
Take it slow!

535
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:07,320
Yeah, just like that!

536
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:09,480
- This is it!
- Run!

537
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:12,280
Keep circling. Yeah!

538
00:38:12,360 --> 00:38:14,000
Hold on, Koh!

539
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:20,080
Koh!

540
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:21,600
Isn't this pathetic? Fighting like this?

541
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:22,560
Hey.

542
00:38:22,640 --> 00:38:24,920
A real man has to stay calm.

543
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:26,960
He doesn't look like a real man.
He looks pathetic.

544
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:28,320
Wanna go up there and fight?

545
00:38:30,200 --> 00:38:31,640
Hey! Jab and back off!

546
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:34,000
- Jab and back off!
- Yeah!

547
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:36,560
Go in, jab, then back off!

548
00:38:37,160 --> 00:38:38,800
Back to your corner!

549
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:41,120
Damn!

550
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:44,720
What was that?

551
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:45,840
Yeah.

552
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:49,560
Good. Keep doing that.

553
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:51,560
He won't fight you. Deal with him.

554
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:52,480
Hey!

555
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:53,600
Go get him.

556
00:38:53,680 --> 00:38:55,800
Are you gonna fight or not?

557
00:38:55,880 --> 00:38:58,840
What do you mean, not fighting?
He landed a few jabs. Didn't you see?

558
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:00,400
Everyone has their own tactics.

559
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:02,280
You call that a tactic?

560
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:03,840
Big body, no guts. You faggot!

561
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:09,560
Back to your corners.

562
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:10,960
Get back to your corner.

563
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:12,080
Back to your corners.

564
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:13,400
Sit down.

565
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:15,640
- Come here.
- Sit down. It's okay.

566
00:39:15,720 --> 00:39:17,400
- Don't listen to him.
- Focus. Come on.

567
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:18,480
Chen, sit down!

568
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:19,920
- This is our game.
- Yeah.

569
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:23,680
Don't listen to him. Stick to the plan.
Hey, give him some water.

570
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:26,520
Chen, keep fighting the same way.
Don't listen to him.

571
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:29,600
You're doing great. Got it?

572
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:30,640
Gao.

573
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:32,960
What do we do now?
At this rate, we're just losing money.

574
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:35,440
Honestly, I'm starting to doubt it too.

575
00:39:35,520 --> 00:39:36,680
Just go with the flow for now.

576
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:38,480
Go with the flow?

577
00:39:38,560 --> 00:39:40,480
Hey, Gao.

578
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:42,320
Did you even have a plan?

579
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:43,920
Didn't you work this out
with Pae beforehand?

580
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:45,840
I did. I just didn't think Pae

581
00:39:45,920 --> 00:39:47,640
would take it this far.

582
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,440
What now, Mr. Wong?

583
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:51,880
Still want to keep going?

584
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:55,680
If you want to bet
the last two million here,

585
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:57,120
I'm fine with that too.

586
00:40:00,760 --> 00:40:01,840
Are you crazy?

587
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:03,960
You'd be insane to keep going.

588
00:40:04,040 --> 00:40:05,800
If you add that to the first five million,

589
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:08,640
you'll lose ten million total, boss.

590
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:11,480
Why do you think I'm going to lose?

591
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:17,160
Well…

592
00:40:19,080 --> 00:40:21,720
No, boss. I just think

593
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:23,520
luck may not be on your side today.

594
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:25,480
If luck isn't on your side,

595
00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:28,960
and you want your lucky ring back,
I'll gladly take it off for you.

596
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:31,640
No! I'm going on, no matter what.

597
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:37,680
Two million.

598
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:40,480
If Unchain wins by knockout
in the next round.

599
00:40:40,560 --> 00:40:42,400
Who said I was betting two million?

600
00:40:50,800 --> 00:40:52,800
This round, I'm betting

601
00:40:52,880 --> 00:40:53,960
ten million!

602
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:54,880
What?

603
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:56,480
Why are you so shocked?

604
00:40:57,720 --> 00:41:00,320
Go get the money bags from the car.

605
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:03,680
Looks like today's going to be a long one.

606
00:41:04,720 --> 00:41:06,800
Yes, Mr. Wong.

607
00:41:08,120 --> 00:41:09,320
Go!

608
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:13,560
Hey, Mr. Kluay.

609
00:41:14,680 --> 00:41:15,840
Where is it,

610
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:17,760
your betting money?

611
00:41:18,720 --> 00:41:22,120
I'm truly sorry, Mr. Wong.
I didn't know you played this big.

612
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:23,360
I didn't bring enough cash.

613
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:25,600
That won't do.

614
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:27,240
This is a bet.

615
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:29,080
The money has to be on the table.

616
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:31,080
We can't just talk.

617
00:41:31,160 --> 00:41:34,320
If it were you, Mr. Kluay,
you wouldn't be happy either.

618
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:40,320
Hey.

619
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:42,120
Go back and get all the money
from the safe

620
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:43,400
at the boxing gym.

621
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:46,040
Boss, isn't that money for Louis?

622
00:41:46,120 --> 00:41:49,520
- We have to pay him tonight.
- Do it. Can't you see he's gone crazy?

623
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:52,000
I'm definitely taking his money.
Tell Nop's guys to come up here too.

624
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:54,400
If these people try anything,

625
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:55,720
we'll wipe them all out.

626
00:41:56,760 --> 00:41:57,560
Yes.

627
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:03,560
I've sent my man to get the cash.

628
00:42:03,640 --> 00:42:06,200
The boxing gym is nearby.
It won't take more than 15 minutes.

629
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:07,640
Wait, boss.

630
00:42:07,720 --> 00:42:09,840
What about the fight?
Are you gonna stop everything

631
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:11,600
and make them wait 15 minutes?

632
00:42:11,680 --> 00:42:13,280
No need. Let's not do that.

633
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:14,560
Don't worry.

634
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,560
I can handle that.

635
00:42:17,640 --> 00:42:18,840
It's not a problem.

636
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:22,360
Same as before, Chen. Stick to the plan.

637
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,040
Round four.

638
00:42:24,120 --> 00:42:26,720
- Be ready.
- Don't listen to him.

639
00:42:31,120 --> 00:42:32,280
The lights went out.

640
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:34,760
Please don't panic.

641
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:37,600
It seems our lighting system
is experiencing a technical issue.

642
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:39,920
Our team is working to fix it now.

643
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:41,600
- Everyone, please remain calm.
- Take a break, Chen.

644
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:42,840
- Back to the locker room?
- Yeah.

645
00:42:46,720 --> 00:42:47,840
Go rest for now.

646
00:42:48,440 --> 00:42:49,480
You okay?

647
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:52,880
- You okay?
- Let's go.

648
00:42:52,960 --> 00:42:55,360
Come on. You okay?

649
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:57,520
Go rest first.

650
00:43:00,400 --> 00:43:03,400
Come on! Keep fighting!

651
00:43:03,480 --> 00:43:05,800
Get the money ready.

652
00:43:06,320 --> 00:43:07,280
Let's go.

653
00:43:07,360 --> 00:43:08,560
Unchain.

654
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:12,680
Hey, what do you want?

655
00:43:12,760 --> 00:43:14,680
Get back to your side!

656
00:43:14,760 --> 00:43:16,440
I remember you now.

657
00:43:17,440 --> 00:43:19,480
You're the guy who went to prison
for assault, right?

658
00:43:22,960 --> 00:43:25,120
I knew your face looked familiar.

659
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:28,040
I'm friends with the guy
you beat half to death.

660
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:35,600
What was your girl's name again?

661
00:43:39,080 --> 00:43:40,360
Right.

662
00:43:40,440 --> 00:43:41,920
Coco.

663
00:43:44,600 --> 00:43:47,720
You said my friend
tried to rape your girl.

664
00:43:48,760 --> 00:43:50,120
That's what she told you, right?

665
00:43:53,280 --> 00:43:55,240
Let me tell you something.

666
00:43:55,320 --> 00:43:57,280
She wanted it.

667
00:44:08,680 --> 00:44:11,080
Don't listen to him.
You don't have to listen to him.

668
00:44:14,600 --> 00:44:15,560
Coco!

669
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:34,400
Who the hell are you?

670
00:44:34,480 --> 00:44:36,920
No, Chen. It's not what you think.

671
00:44:40,160 --> 00:44:42,320
Listen to me. Please.

672
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:44,440
Don't tell me that's your husband.

673
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:48,400
Tell him.

674
00:44:48,480 --> 00:44:49,800
Tell him you're working.

675
00:44:56,440 --> 00:44:58,520
Big guy for nothing.

676
00:44:59,040 --> 00:45:00,240
You faggot!

677
00:45:08,720 --> 00:45:10,200
- Drag him out.
- Please, listen to me.

678
00:45:10,280 --> 00:45:11,600
Get him out of here, now!

679
00:45:12,960 --> 00:45:14,280
He raped me.

680
00:45:17,480 --> 00:45:19,120
He raped me.

681
00:45:19,200 --> 00:45:20,520
Drag him out!

682
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:25,840
- Hey, you!
- What's your problem?

683
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:31,120
Chen.

684
00:45:31,200 --> 00:45:33,360
Don't listen to him.

685
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:35,200
Your girl Coco,

686
00:45:35,280 --> 00:45:36,440
she's just a call girl.

687
00:45:36,520 --> 00:45:38,760
An escort. You know that, right?

688
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:41,400
Chen! Don't!

689
00:45:42,080 --> 00:45:42,960
Hey, don't!

690
00:45:43,040 --> 00:45:44,960
Hey! Get back to your corner!

691
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:46,560
- Let's go, Chen.
- Don't, Chen!

692
00:45:46,640 --> 00:45:48,680
- Come on, Chen.
- Angpao.

693
00:45:48,760 --> 00:45:49,720
- Yes?
- Take him away!

694
00:45:53,760 --> 00:45:55,800
Mr. Kluay, how much longer

695
00:45:55,880 --> 00:45:57,120
until your money gets here?

696
00:45:57,800 --> 00:45:59,360
Not long, Mr. Wong.

697
00:45:59,440 --> 00:46:00,280
Calm down.

698
00:46:00,360 --> 00:46:03,440
I'm afraid the fighters
will cool off first.

699
00:46:04,160 --> 00:46:05,120
Let's do this.

700
00:46:06,520 --> 00:46:08,160
I trust you, Mr. Kluay.

701
00:46:08,840 --> 00:46:11,080
You don't have to put the money down.

702
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:13,600
Let the fight continue.

703
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:17,760
Are you serious, boss?

704
00:46:17,840 --> 00:46:20,400
This round is ten million.

705
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:24,240
I'm fine either way.

706
00:46:24,320 --> 00:46:26,520
If you want the fight to continue,
I'm okay with that.

707
00:46:27,520 --> 00:46:29,160
Then turn the lights back on.

708
00:46:41,200 --> 00:46:44,920
Alright, everyone.
The arena lights are back on.

709
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:47,640
In just a moment, our main event

710
00:46:47,720 --> 00:46:49,880
will continue.

711
00:47:00,320 --> 00:47:01,560
Fighters, come here.

712
00:47:02,440 --> 00:47:03,440
Come here.

713
00:47:04,320 --> 00:47:05,360
Okay.

714
00:47:12,280 --> 00:47:13,920
Now I believe it.

715
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:15,720
You've got some serious guts.

716
00:47:19,960 --> 00:47:20,960
Fight!

717
00:47:33,040 --> 00:47:33,800
Exactly!

718
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:36,040
Fight!

719
00:47:40,400 --> 00:47:42,680
Hey, Chen! Why are you
trading punches with him?

720
00:47:44,400 --> 00:47:46,000
Chen, back off! You're gonna go down!

721
00:47:48,840 --> 00:47:50,000
Fight!

722
00:47:51,600 --> 00:47:52,960
Don't!

723
00:47:57,120 --> 00:47:57,960
Back to your corner!

724
00:48:03,400 --> 00:48:04,800
Chen!

725
00:48:09,680 --> 00:48:10,720
Hey.

726
00:48:23,480 --> 00:48:24,800
Koh, why is Chen…

727
00:48:34,800 --> 00:48:36,800
His eco mode's been unlocked.

728
00:48:37,440 --> 00:48:39,040
That's what scares me about him.

729
00:48:40,080 --> 00:48:41,680
Yes!

730
00:48:41,760 --> 00:48:42,600
Fight!

731
00:48:48,400 --> 00:48:49,480
Guard up!

732
00:48:56,720 --> 00:48:57,560
Fight!

733
00:49:27,720 --> 00:49:28,600
Chen!

734
00:49:28,680 --> 00:49:30,160
- Back to your corner!
- Chen!

735
00:49:31,720 --> 00:49:33,600
Looks like it'll end this round.

736
00:49:43,240 --> 00:49:44,400
Hold!

737
00:49:44,480 --> 00:49:46,640
- Chen! You okay?
- Chen!

738
00:49:49,440 --> 00:49:51,320
- One.
- Chen!

739
00:49:51,400 --> 00:49:53,120
- Chen! Hey!
- Chen!

740
00:49:53,200 --> 00:49:55,320
Get up! Chen!

741
00:49:56,720 --> 00:49:58,000
Chen!

742
00:49:58,080 --> 00:49:59,160
- Chen!
- Chen!

743
00:49:59,240 --> 00:50:01,000
- Get up!
- Chen!

744
00:50:01,720 --> 00:50:03,000
- Chen! Hey!
- Chen!

745
00:50:03,520 --> 00:50:04,560
Chen!

746
00:50:09,360 --> 00:50:10,680
<i>Chen.</i>

747
00:50:12,120 --> 00:50:13,400
<i>Chen.</i>

748
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:16,120
<i>Chen.</i>

749
00:50:16,760 --> 00:50:17,840
Babe.

750
00:50:20,560 --> 00:50:21,920
Wake up already.

751
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:27,040
Chen.

752
00:50:31,120 --> 00:50:34,040
You said you'd get up today
and make me dessert.

753
00:50:41,840 --> 00:50:46,240
Babe, can I sleep a little longer?
I'm so comfy right now.

754
00:50:51,880 --> 00:50:53,520
- Chen!
- Chen!

755
00:50:53,600 --> 00:50:55,760
Chen! Hey!

756
00:50:55,840 --> 00:50:57,240
Chen!

757
00:50:57,840 --> 00:50:59,800
Chen! Get up!

758
00:50:59,880 --> 00:51:02,160
<i>No, you can't sleep anymore.</i>

759
00:51:03,120 --> 00:51:04,960
If you don't wake up,

760
00:51:05,040 --> 00:51:06,640
that means you don't love me.

761
00:51:06,720 --> 00:51:09,000
Don't you love me, Chen?

762
00:51:09,560 --> 00:51:11,000
I do love you.

763
00:51:11,080 --> 00:51:13,360
<i>If you love me, then wake up.</i>

764
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:16,440
Wake up right now!

765
00:51:29,360 --> 00:51:32,400
- Chen!
- Hey!

766
00:51:32,480 --> 00:51:34,240
Quick, get up, Chen!

767
00:51:34,320 --> 00:51:36,080
Hey, go to your corner.

768
00:51:38,080 --> 00:51:39,480
- He's awake!
- Chen!

769
00:51:40,760 --> 00:51:42,760
- Chen!
- Chen

770
00:51:42,840 --> 00:51:44,440
He can still get up?

771
00:51:45,040 --> 00:51:46,920
Of course he can. My Unchain!

772
00:51:48,080 --> 00:51:50,760
Why are you so happy? Did you forget?

773
00:51:50,840 --> 00:51:52,560
Unchain has to win by knockout

774
00:51:52,640 --> 00:51:53,960
to get the money on this table.

775
00:52:01,560 --> 00:52:02,720
Shark, your mouthguard.

776
00:52:02,800 --> 00:52:03,880
No need.

777
00:52:04,720 --> 00:52:05,840
Ready.

778
00:52:07,120 --> 00:52:08,240
You okay?

779
00:52:11,920 --> 00:52:13,040
Ready.

780
00:52:13,120 --> 00:52:14,080
Fight!

781
00:52:17,280 --> 00:52:18,840
You're pretty tough,

782
00:52:18,920 --> 00:52:20,240
huh?

783
00:52:23,240 --> 00:52:24,520
If you're this tough,

784
00:52:25,120 --> 00:52:26,640
why did your girl become an escort?

785
00:52:26,720 --> 00:52:27,800
Huh?

786
00:52:30,360 --> 00:52:32,320
You just couldn't satisfy her,

787
00:52:32,400 --> 00:52:33,320
right?

788
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:47,320
Maybe your girl just couldn't get enough!

789
00:53:07,640 --> 00:53:11,800
Chen!

790
00:53:11,880 --> 00:53:16,760
- Yes!
- Yes!

791
00:53:21,400 --> 00:53:22,400
- Boss!
- Yes!

792
00:53:22,480 --> 00:53:24,680
We did it!

793
00:53:29,840 --> 00:53:31,880
Don't tell me
we're getting all this money?

794
00:53:31,960 --> 00:53:34,560
Yes!

795
00:53:34,640 --> 00:53:35,680
Five.

796
00:53:36,360 --> 00:53:37,200
Six.

797
00:53:37,280 --> 00:53:38,320
Seven.

798
00:53:38,400 --> 00:53:39,760
- Eight.
- It's confirmed.

799
00:53:41,040 --> 00:53:42,000
- Nine.
- Hey!

800
00:53:42,800 --> 00:53:44,400
- And…
- Whoa!

801
00:53:44,480 --> 00:53:46,560
The power's out. What happened?

802
00:53:49,920 --> 00:53:51,520
Who turned off the lights?

803
00:53:51,600 --> 00:53:53,520
Hey, Mr. Kluay!

804
00:53:54,040 --> 00:53:55,160
What's going on?

805
00:53:55,240 --> 00:53:56,760
My fighter was about to win.

806
00:53:56,840 --> 00:53:58,240
Why did the lights go out?

807
00:53:59,760 --> 00:54:01,040
What's that?

808
00:54:02,080 --> 00:54:04,240
You ordered the blackout, didn't you?

809
00:54:05,400 --> 00:54:07,240
Huh? Are you trying to cheat me?

810
00:54:07,320 --> 00:54:08,960
Why would you say that?

811
00:54:09,040 --> 00:54:10,440
The power went out on its own.

812
00:54:11,040 --> 00:54:13,160
So this fight is void.

813
00:54:15,680 --> 00:54:17,640
I won't accept that. Hong.

814
00:54:18,320 --> 00:54:19,760
Take my share of the money.

815
00:54:20,360 --> 00:54:22,200
We're leaving.

816
00:54:25,440 --> 00:54:27,880
- What the hell?
- Calm down.

817
00:54:29,080 --> 00:54:31,160
If you want to leave, go ahead.

818
00:54:31,760 --> 00:54:33,920
But don't touch the money on this table.

819
00:54:37,920 --> 00:54:38,960
Fine.

820
00:54:39,600 --> 00:54:41,040
But remember this.

821
00:54:42,440 --> 00:54:43,440
You!

822
00:54:44,080 --> 00:54:47,000
You're as easy as your name, Kluay!

823
00:54:49,440 --> 00:54:51,160
Let's go, Hong.

824
00:54:54,640 --> 00:54:56,280
What the hell is he talking about?

825
00:54:57,400 --> 00:54:58,800
Crazy bastard.

826
00:55:02,640 --> 00:55:05,880
Yak, call everyone and tell them to run.
We'll meet at base.

827
00:55:05,960 --> 00:55:06,840
Wait.

828
00:55:06,920 --> 00:55:09,360
I don't get it. Why do we have to run?

829
00:55:09,440 --> 00:55:11,960
We didn't get the money,
and that bastard Kluay cheated us.

830
00:55:12,040 --> 00:55:15,360
Who said we didn't get the money, Hong?
Because all four bags

831
00:55:15,960 --> 00:55:17,440
are full of cash.

832
00:55:18,320 --> 00:55:20,120
What do you mean?

833
00:55:22,240 --> 00:55:23,240
Whoa, the lights!

834
00:55:23,320 --> 00:55:24,480
Who turned off the lights?

835
00:55:24,560 --> 00:55:26,240
<i>It means when he ordered the blackout,</i>

836
00:55:26,320 --> 00:55:28,240
the two of us switched the bags.

837
00:55:28,320 --> 00:55:30,560
We got them good.

838
00:55:31,760 --> 00:55:32,600
Really?

839
00:55:32,680 --> 00:55:34,200
Excuse me, idiots.

840
00:55:34,280 --> 00:55:37,400
Are we going to wait for them
to figure it out and escape too late?

841
00:55:37,480 --> 00:55:38,840
Talk in the car.

842
00:55:38,920 --> 00:55:39,920
- Move.
- I'll call them.

843
00:55:40,000 --> 00:55:40,920
- Go!
- Hey!

844
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:43,320
Pao. Split up and run.

845
00:55:43,400 --> 00:55:46,760
- How did the lights go out?
- How did this happen?

846
00:55:46,840 --> 00:55:49,360
- Why are the lights out?
- Whoa, the lights are out!

847
00:55:49,440 --> 00:55:51,760
Boss, downstairs is asking
if we can turn the lights back on.

848
00:55:53,640 --> 00:55:55,520
Hey, turn the lights back on now.

849
00:55:57,920 --> 00:55:59,880
Hello, test.

850
00:55:59,960 --> 00:56:03,040
We sincerely apologize
for the inconvenience.

851
00:56:03,120 --> 00:56:04,600
Our lighting system

852
00:56:04,680 --> 00:56:06,640
had a technical issue.

853
00:56:06,720 --> 00:56:09,040
After consulting with the team,

854
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:12,000
we'd like to inform everyone

855
00:56:12,080 --> 00:56:14,960
that today's fight

856
00:56:15,040 --> 00:56:16,160
must be postponed.

857
00:56:20,080 --> 00:56:24,360
- Unchain!
- Unchain!

858
00:56:29,360 --> 00:56:30,840
That's enough to impress them?

859
00:56:30,920 --> 00:56:34,680
- Unchain!
- Unchain!

860
00:56:40,640 --> 00:56:42,040
Where did he go?

861
00:56:42,120 --> 00:56:43,440
Do you know

862
00:56:43,520 --> 00:56:45,720
how much bad press your business

863
00:56:45,800 --> 00:56:47,080
is getting?

864
00:56:47,160 --> 00:56:49,040
Help me get out of here first.

865
00:56:49,120 --> 00:56:50,400
Whatever you want,

866
00:56:50,480 --> 00:56:51,680
I'll pay anything.

867
00:56:51,760 --> 00:56:54,240
<i>Once he's sent to detention,</i>
<i>finish him off.</i>

868
00:56:55,080 --> 00:56:56,120
<i>See you, boss.</i>

869
00:56:56,200 --> 00:56:57,960
I want to know
if my father is still alive.

870
00:56:58,040 --> 00:57:00,640
If he's already dead,
I won't have to keep waiting like this.

871
00:57:00,720 --> 00:57:01,720
What if he isn't dead?

872
00:57:01,800 --> 00:57:04,160
Then I'd probably ask him
why he abandoned me that day.

873
00:57:04,240 --> 00:57:06,040
I think Risa is Aek's daughter.

874
00:57:06,120 --> 00:57:07,640
Let's look at the target for this mission.

875
00:57:07,720 --> 00:57:10,560
Her name is Mam Yollada Arayasai,

876
00:57:10,640 --> 00:57:12,400
owner of M Power Group.

877
00:57:12,480 --> 00:57:14,480
On the surface,
it's an investment company.

878
00:57:14,560 --> 00:57:17,960
But in reality, it's a pyramid scheme.

879
00:58:02,240 --> 00:58:04,240
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
